Job Posting End Date
October 14, 2024
Job Location
Rutherford
Job Description
Fulton Hogan are currently looking to expand our Spray Seal team based in Rutherford as we start to build our team for upcoming works. Our goal is to create a highly skilled team who will deliver quality spray seal projects to a diverse client portfolio within the region, with a strong focus on our “Living Safely” culture and REAL values.
Our people share the same set of values that keep us REAL. Respect, Energy and Effort, Attitude and Leadership encapsulates what we stand for at Fulton Hogan and encourage us to foster a diverse and inclusive culture where we listen to, care for, celebrate, and respect everyone.*What’s on offer?*
An opportunity to get your foot on the door on a well-established company working in the civil construction industry. We are seeking for a motivated, reliable and hardworking Crew Member / Labourer to join our spray sealing crews.*How you’ll connect to the role?*
To be successful in this position you will require the following skills/experience;* Hold a current Full Car licence;
* Have relevant industry cards, e.g. Construction Induction Card (White Card);
* Are available to work overtime, weekends, or to live and travel away from home as required;
* A positive attitude, self-motivation and the ability to work effectively as part of a team;
* Possess a strong commitment to safety;
* Be willing to be flexible and adaptable for a multitude of tasks;
* Be a strong team player, reliable and hard-working.
* Someone who enjoys an outdoor working environment.


While not essential, it is advantageous if you;* Have previous experience in the civil or road construction industry;
* Hold a current MR, HR, HC licence;
* Have licence(s) on mobile plant, e.g. roller or front end loader;
* Spotters, First Aid; Traffic Control.

*On the job training will be provided\\**
The pre-employment process will involve a medical check including drug and alcohol screening.* Want to be paid well for the Good Work you do? Apply now to learn more about the applicable hourly rate and allowances.
* Living Safely: We place people at the heart of everything we do because everyone has the right to go home safely. We have an unrelenting focus on the effective management of critical risks and take personal responsibility for keeping ourselves and others safe.
* Keen to progress your career? We invest in our people and provide career development pathways by offering apprenticeships, traineeship, and certificate(s) opportunities. If additional tickets & licenses are required, we can help with that too.
* Looking to enhance your wellbeing? We offer great benefits, including corporate health and fitness programs, health insurance discounts, personal banking support, and a range of retailer discounts. We also provide access to our Employee Assistance Program (including your immediate family).

* Want to help us better the communities we live and work in? Our purpose of *creating, connecting, and caring for communities* is more than a saying to us – it’s a way of thinking, working, and living because we're locals too, and seek to give back in ways that strengthen and build resilient communities. You’ll find us partnering with local and national community groups, like Clontarf Foundation, Black Dog Institute, and Soldier On, in addition to indigenous groups and social enterprises, to ensure that our good work positively impacts and brings about sustainable change within our industry.


If our REAL values resonate with you, please submit an application for the position. If you’re not sure that you meet 100% of the selection criteria, that’s okay, we would still like to hear from you and potentially discuss how your skills could be utilised at Fulton Hogan.*For 90 years, Fulton Hogan has been delivering high-quality infrastructure to improve the lives of people every day. Our 10,000+ team works in every kind of weather and environment, creating, connecting, and caring for communities across Australia and New Zealand.* *We celebrate and embrace diversity across our business and are committed to equal employment opportunities.**We believe in the value that diversity brings to our team and people who share our REAL values are encouraged to apply*

**Position summary****:**  



The Manager, Major Gifts helps donors accomplish their philanthropic goals and ambitions through a relationship with the Rainforest Alliance. They are responsible for identifying, qualifying, cultivating, soliciting, and stewarding new prospects and individual donors with Major Giving potential ($10,000+ annually).  



Reporting to the Senior Director of Individual Giving, this position works closely with the Individual Giving team, alongside Prospect Research, Annual Fund, and other teams to collaborate on fundraising opportunities and donor qualification strategies. They represent the Rainforest Alliance externally and continually build strong relationships with prospects and existing donors. They develop and execute cultivation strategies for current and prospective major donors and work closely with Prospect Research on the donor qualification process. They develop strategies that include direct solicitation and hold cultivation meetings that will lead to major gifts. They write proposals for unrestricted and restricted solicitations in coordination with teams in the field, ensuring messaging to donors shows the true impact of their funding. In partnership with the Senior Director, Individual Giving, they help execute a stewardship plan for a portfolio of Major Gift donors and work with the Revenue Operations team to maximize fundraising potential in new and emerging markets.  



**Responsibilities****:**


* Act as primary manager for a portfolio of donors giving between $10,000 and $50,000, to move current and prospective donors toward solicitation; balancing portfolio management between discovery, cultivation, solicitation, and stewardship;
* Develop and implement a comprehensive strategy for all donors and prospects within their portfolio to raise awareness of RA’s mission and broaden RA’s funding base;
* Cultivate and expand planned giving opportunities with new and existing donors, and integrate planned gift stewardship into broader stewardship efforts;
* Work with the Senior Editorial Associate to develop externally-facing major gift materials;
* Plan and implement events and activities for portfolio of individual major gift donors to engage in networking activities, as well as opportunities to generate potential prospects for cultivation;
* Maintain up-to-date revenue projections toward annual revenue goals;
* Track and report relationship management activity using Salesforce;
* Build and analyze reports in Salesforce to report progress against cultivation, stewardship, and fundraising goals;
* Develop and maintain strong collaborative working relationships with other team members;
* Perform related duties as assigned.





**Qualifications****:**


* College degree required;
* 3-5 years of successful, demonstrated experience in major and planned gift fundraising, preferably in conservation, climate, or environment;
* Strong written, oral, and presentation communication skills, and have experience in developing clear and concise funding proposals;
* Demonstrated success in meeting financial goals for major gift giving, with a proven track record of cultivating and securing five-figure gifts and above, and successful experience in making cold calls, as well as developing cultivation and solicitation strategies;
* Strong interpersonal skills and the ability to build and maintain relationships with major gift donors and multiple stakeholders;
* Experience with Development databases, preferably Salesforce.





**Job level:** 3A  



**Salary:** For USA based candidates only:


* + **National Salary range (Excluding NY and DC) -**$62,950- $89,899
	+ **New York Salary Range -**$74,768- $106,811
	+ **Washington DC Salary Range -**$72,369- $103,384



**Deadline:** 27 September 2024  



**Notes:** Only candidates authorized to work in locations where we are registered will be considered.  



**If you have any questions about the job vacancy, please contact the HR department:** **recruitment@ra.org**




**WHO WE ARE:**  



The Rainforest Alliance is creating a more sustainable world by using social and market forces to protect nature and improve the lives of farmers and forest communities. To achieve our mission, we partner with diverse allies around the world to drive positive change across global supply chains and in many of our most critically important natural landscapes.  



Our alliance spans 70 countries and includes farmers and forest communities, companies, governments, civil society, and millions of individuals. Together we work to protect forests and biodiversity, take action on climate, and promote the rights and improve the livelihoods of rural people.  



As an international nonprofit organization with more than 30 years of experience in sustainability transformation, we understand that the social and economic well-being of rural communities is tightly connected to ecosystem health. This knowledge has shaped our rigorous programs to advance sustainable land-use and commodity production.  



At the Rainforest Alliance we combat climate change, protect forests and biodiversity, promote human rights, and improve livelihoods. The enormity of the social and environmental challenges we are facing requires working together in a broad alliance. This is why we bring farmers, forest communities, companies, and consumers together to change the way the world produces, sources, and consumes.  



**Why**  

To protect nature and improve lives it’s becoming increasingly urgent that we approach the way we use our land and produce food and other products in more sustainable ways. For this to succeed we need to fundamentally change the way that businesses operate and source, and the choices we all make as consumers.  



**How**  

Our growing global alliance aims to transform our relationship with our natural resources and each other, to create a better future for people and nature together.  



**The Rainforest Alliance encourages diversity and inclusion across the global organization. With this commitment to diversity, we are proud to be an equal opportunity employer and do not discriminate on the basis of gender, race, color, ethnicity, religion, sexual orientation, gender identity, ages, disability, and any other protected group.**
